19 The effect of these provisions is as follows:


 • where there is a shortfall amount the Commissioner is required to identify the cause of the shortfall amount, and apply the appropriate percentage to arrive at the base penalty amount;
 • accordingly, once the cause has been identified, the taxpayer is liable to pay the applicable penalty (for example, 50% of the shortfall amount in circumstances where the shortfall resulted from recklessness);
 • at this stage in the process there is no discretion in the Commissioner as to the imposition of the relevant penalty - the amount of the penalty flows from the cause of the shortfall, based on the culpability of the behaviour of the taxpayer or tax agent.

This is because:


 • Explanatory Memorandum 2000 specifically refers to reforms to the administrative penalty regime in Pt 4.25 and specifically s 298- 20 ;
 • Explanatory Memorandum 2000 was prepared in the context of the package of legislation comprising the new tax system (paras 1.3-1.5);
 • the provisions of Div 284 postdate Div 298, and it appears that a reason for the extensive discussion in Explanatory Memorandum 2000 concerning Div 298 was to explain the manner in which it was intended to operate in the context of the penalties imposed by Div 284.
